.TH "fbtft_framebuffer_alloc" 9 "fbtft_framebuffer_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fbtft_framebuffer_alloc \- creates a new frame buffer info structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct fb_info *" fbtft_framebuffer_alloc
.BI "(struct fbtft_display *display "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct fbtft_platform_data *pdata "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "display" 12
pointer to structure describing the display
.IP "dev" 12
pointer to the device for this fb, this can be NULL
.IP "pdata" 12
platform data for the display in use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates a new frame buffer info structure.

Also creates and populates the following structures:
info->fbops
info->fbdefio
info->pseudo_palette
par->fbtftops
par->txbuf

Returns the new structure, or NULL if an error occurred.
